"{\n  \"text\": \"This is how I make bone broth. I start with a little bit of vinegar. I add my bones, always getting uh grass-fed bones because you're looking to get the essence out of them, so you want the good nutritious bones. This is the first, second, third day of boiling, and it gets a little bit richer, a little bit darker. The fat renders a little bit more, the marrow renders a little bit more every day. And then at the end of it, it's time to harvest. I let it cool it a little bit. I pull out some of the fat and the marrow and all the good stuff, and then I pull out the bones. This is a little bit of uh both, and I take the bones, I crunch them all up and get them ready because I give them to the chickens. Uh they crumble like chalk. Uh, bone broth is a great way to rebuild the gut, and it's a good starting step for people who are dealing with uh sensitivities or just having a bad time with things. Uh, this is my bone broth without the fat distributed. You notice it's all different levels, and so I'll take some of that fat and I'll distribute it out. And what you'll see here is at the end of it, they're all nice and level, ready to go, and then I just put them in a crate, stick them in my fridge.\",\n  \"sentences\": [\n    {\n      \"text\": \" This is how I make bone broth.\",\n      \"start\": 0.24,\n      \"end\": 1.68,\n      \"duration\": 1.44,\n      \"confidence\": 0.996,\n      \"tokens\": [\n        {\n          \"text\": \" This\",\n          \"start\": 0.24,\n          \"end\": 0.4,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n          \"confidence\": 0.997\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \" is\",\n          \"start\": 0.4,\n          \"end\": 0.48,\n          \"duration\": 0.08,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \" how\",\n          \"start\": 0.48,\n          \"end\": 0.64,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \" I\",\n          \"sta